[Event "Wijk aan Zee — Kasparov's Immortal"]
[Site "Wijk aan Zee"]
[Date "1999.01.20"]
[White "Garry Kasparov"]
[Black "Veselin Topalov"]
[Result "1-0"]
[Blurb "Widely called the greatest game of the modern era. Kasparov sacrifices a rook to drag Topalov's king on a march from b8 all the way across the board — and calculates the whole hunt to mate."]

1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. Be3 Bg7 5. Qd2 c6 6. f3 b5 {A Pirc where both sides castle into opposite corners — the recipe for a race.}
7. Nge2 Nbd7 8. Bh6 Bxh6 9. Qxh6 Bb7 10. a3 e5 11. O-O-O Qe7
12. Kb1 a6 13. Nc1 O-O-O 14. Nb3 exd4 15. Rxd4 c5 16. Rd1 Nb6 17. g3 Kb8 18. Na5 Ba8 19. Bh3 d5
20. Qf4+ Ka7 21. Rhe1 d4 22. Nd5 Nbxd5 23. exd5 Qd6 {The tension is unbearable; Kasparov now unleashes it.}
24. Rxd4 {The first blow — the rook is offered to blow open Black's king.} cxd4 25. Re7+ Kb6 26. Qxd4+ Kxa5 {The king is forced out into the open, and the hunt begins.}
27. b4+ Ka4 28. Qc3 Qxd5 29. Ra7 Bb7 30. Rxb7 Qc4 31. Qxf6 Kxa3 32. Qxa6+ Kxb4 33. c3+ Kxc3 34. Qa1+ Kd2 35. Qb2+ Kd1 {Topalov's king has walked from b8 to d1 under a hail of checks.}
36. Bf1 Rd2 37. Rd7 Rxd7 38. Bxc4 bxc4 39. Qxh8 Rd3 40. Qa8 c3 41. Qa4+ Ke1 42. f4 f5 43. Kc1 Rd2 44. Qa7 {Black resigned. The king hunt Kasparov saw from move 24 comes home a piece up and winning. A masterpiece of calculation.}
